# Cloudflare Pages routing.
#
# We deliberately keep NO client-route rewrites here and emit no dist/404.html
# (see scripts/prerender.mjs). With neither present, Pages stays in its default
# single-page-app fallback: any request that does not match a static file is
# served the app shell (index.html) at HTTP 200, and the client router renders
# the correct page.
#
# Do NOT re-add "/route /index.html 200" rules: Pages canonicalizes the
# /index.html rewrite target to "/", turning those rewrites into a "308 -> /"
# that bounces every app route (/login, /register, /dashboard, ...) to the
# homepage and locks users out. This file exists only to document that.
#
# Prerendered marketing/legal pages are physical files in dist/ and are served
# directly before any fallback runs.
